The short version: use it however you like, just don't re-release it.


YOU MAY

1. Use the mod for any purpose, private or public, including on public and
   commercial servers, with no permission needed and no fee.

2. Include the mod in a modpack, public or private, free or paid, provided
   that the modpack credits "BuildRush by WCG" and links to
   https://github.com/lapizwcg/buildrush

3. Read, study and modify the source code for your own use, and distribute
   modifications as patches or pull requests against the official repository.

4. Make and keep copies for backup and personal use.


YOU MAY NOT

1. Re-release the mod. This means: uploading it, in whole or in part, in
   original or modified form, to any site, store, launcher, repository or
   distribution platform other than the official repository above.

2. Publish a modified or renamed version of the mod as a separate project.

3. Remove or alter authorship, license or attribution.

4. Sell the mod itself, or put access to the mod behind a paywall.
   (Charging for a server or a modpack that includes it is fine — see above.)


NOTES

- Point 2 under YOU MAY is a deliberate exception to "no re-release": modpacks
  are how mods find their audience. Referencing the mod so the launcher
  downloads it from the official page is always preferred over bundling the
  jar, but bundling is permitted under the conditions above.

